AC Milan are reportedly set to appoint Stefano Pioli as their new manager, after sacking Marco Giampaolo. 56-year old, Marco Giampaolo has coached, Empoli F.C, U.C Sampdoria before joining the Serie A club, A.C The Swiss-born Italian former professional footballer and former manager’s time at the club has come to an end after also failing to impress fans with his transfer business. Fabrizio Romano claims the Italian giants have sacked Marco Giampaolo after their dismal start to the new campaign. Milan have won three and lost four of their opening seven Serie A games. Milan sit 13th in the Serie A table, having lost four of their opening seven fixtures, including a 2-0 defeat by rivals Inter. 